sentences.english: The next morning, nurse Wu came to Mr. Chen's bedside.
sentences.chinese: 第二天早晨，吳來到了陳的病牀邊。

sentences.english: WuHuaLan first time to call shunde, the report good thereafter.
sentences.chinese: 吳華蘭第一時間打電話給順德，報告好音訊。

sentences.english: They fell to praising Aunt Wu warmly.
sentences.chinese: 他們都熱情地誇起吳大嬸來。

sentences.english: Wu said she makes just a few cents on each one.
sentences.chinese: 吳女士說她從每個嗚嗚祖啦上僅僅賺幾美分。

sentences.english: Stephanie Ng is a Ph. D. student in Hong Kong Baptist University.
sentences.chinese: 吳月華，香港浸會大學電影學院研究生。

sentences.english: "Financial markets are poor multi-taskers, " Woo writes.
sentences.chinese: “金融市場的多任務處理能力較差，”吳寫到。

sentences.english: The cook put down his knife and told Master Wu about this strange turtle.
sentences.chinese: 廚子放下刀，告訴吳少爺這隻奇龜。

sentences.english: Mrs. Wu will have the filet mignon with baked potato and Caesar salad.
sentences.chinese: 吳太太要小牛排，加烤馬鈴薯和凱撒沙拉。

sentences.english: Miss Wu had a good idea to solve the problem.
sentences.chinese: 吳老師有一個好辦法解決這個問題。

sentences.english: Some southern states, such as Chu and Wu, claimed independence from the Zhou.
sentences.chinese: 一些南方國家，如楚，吳，聲稱獨立於周。

sentences.english: Wu Yuegui was going to break off an engagement, and the road met gold rings and purples.
sentences.chinese: 吳月桂要到楊家退婚，路上遇見金環與嫣紅。

sentences.english: Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister Wu Hailong attended the meeting.
sentences.chinese: 中國外交部部長助理吳海龍出席。

sentences.english: Mr Wu wants me to give a talk in class tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 吳老師想讓我在明天的課上作一個報告。

sentences.english: Mr. Wu teaches two classes. He likes to compare Class Three with Class Five.
sentences.chinese: 吳老師教兩個班，他喜歡拿三班和五班做比較。

sentences.english: Wu was hospitalized after his face turned black, the paper said.
sentences.chinese: 吳臉色發黑之後被送往醫院治療，該報紙稱。

sentences.english: You can tell Miss Wu about this.She can deal with it.
sentences.chinese: 你可以把這事告訴吳老師，她會處理的。
